In a press conference, President Biden addressed the impact of Putin's actions in Ukraine on gas prices in the United States. He emphasized the need to increase the supply of oil to lower gas prices and reduce dependence on foreign oil. Biden called on U.S. oil companies to use their profits to increase production and pass on the savings to consumers. He also announced the release of 1 million barrels per day from the Strategic Petroleum Reserve for the next six months. Additionally, Biden discussed his long-term plan for American energy independence, which includes transitioning to clean energy and reducing dependence on fossil fuels. He highlighted the potential cost savings for American families through the adoption of electric vehicles and cleaner electricity. Biden also mentioned using the Defense Production Act to secure critical materials for clean energy technologies. He urged Congress to pass his plan and emphasized the importance of taking action to protect American families from rising gas prices.